collectionItem.content:
A group of men aggrieved with their wives held an agitation here in Maharashtra, demanding laws against "injustice" they face at home, and took 108 anti-clockwise rounds around a peepal tree, praying not to get the same life partner again.

Some men not happy with their spouses formed a 'patni peedit' ashram in Aurangabad a few years back to raise their grievances.

The Maharashtra Cyber Cell, in an overnight operation, arrested five recovery agents of a Karnataka-based loan shark mobile application for allegedly blackmailing, harassing and cheating several people across India.

The accused have been remanded to police custody and are charged under relevant sections for defamation and extortion under the IPC and Information Technology Act.

collectionItem.content:
The Bombay High Court refused to allow Maharashtra cabinet minister Nawab Malik's plea to be amended, after which his lawyers stated that they would withdraw the plea.

Malik had previously filed a petition seeking permission to vote in the Rajya Sabha election on June 10. However, after a special court under the Prevention of Money Laundering Act (PMLA) refused to grant Malik any relief on June 9, his lawyers filed a petition challenging the order concerning the Rajya Sabha election. Malik's legal team made a last-minute request to Justice PD Naik, but it was denied.

On Monday, advocates Taraq Sayed and Kushal Mor said that they wanted to amend their earlier petition and that "there is substantial amendment as there is a fresh election of the Maharashtra Legislative Council (MLC) on June 20."

However, Justice PD Naik said, "You have to file a fresh petition.
